Title:  Counterpoint Gun Control Is Constitutional 
Virginia s version later copied by New York and North Carolina brought together three elements in one article affirmation of a right to bear arms reliance on state militia and opposition to a standing army That the people have a right to keep and bear arms that a well regulated militia composed of the body of the people trained to arms is the proper natural and safe defense of a free state that standing armies in times of peace are dangerous to liberty and therefore ought to be avoided. . . 
